@page "/templates/invoice-template-excel"
@inject ProductBranding Branding

<PageTitle>Excel Invoice Template for Small Business - @Branding.SiteName</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Preview an Excel invoice template landing page from ExcelToolStack for small business billing, service invoices, line items, totals, tax, notes, and payment-ready handoff." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="@($"{Branding.SiteUrl}/templates/invoice-template-excel")" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="@($"Excel invoice template for small business - {Branding.SiteName}")" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="A public preview of a polished Excel invoice template page for billing, line items, taxes, totals, payment notes, and client-ready invoices." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="tool-hero template-hero">
    <div class="tool-hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Excel invoice template</p>
        <h1>A clean invoice template for client-ready spreadsheet billing.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
            Preview the first @Branding.SiteName template landing page: a professional Excel invoice structure
            for service businesses, consultants, freelancers, and teams that need clear billing without heavy software.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button button--primary" href="/templates">Back to templates</a>
            <a class="button button--secondary" href="/pricing">View pricing preview</a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-proof" aria-label="Invoice template highlights">
            <span>Line items</span>
            <span>Taxes and totals</span>
            <span>Client notes</span>
            <span>Excel-ready structure</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="invoice-preview" aria-label="Excel invoice template mockup">
        <div class="invoice-preview-header">
            <strong>Invoice</strong>
            <span>#1048</span>
        </div>
        <div class="invoice-meta">
            <span>Client</span>
            <strong>Northwind Studio</strong>
            <span>Due</span>
            <strong>Net 15</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="invoice-table">
            <div class="invoice-row invoice-row--head">
                <span>Description</span>
                <span>Qty</span>
                <span>Total</span>
            </div>
            <div class="invoice-row">
                <span>Strategy workshop</span>
                <span>1</span>
                <span>$1,200</span>
            </div>
            <div class="invoice-row">
                <span>Implementation support</span>
                <span>8</span>
                <span>$1,600</span>
            </div>
            <div class="invoice-row">
                <span>Reporting setup</span>
                <span>1</span>
                <span>$650</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="invoice-total">
            <span>Amount due</span>
            <strong>$3,450.00</strong>
        </div>
        <p>No download is connected yet. This is a static template preview for SEO and product positioning.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell section-shell--tight">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Use cases</p>
        <h2>Built for the everyday invoice workflows spreadsheets still handle well.</h2>
        <p>
            This public page positions the future template around practical billing jobs, without adding file
            generation, payments, uploads, account gates, or backend logic.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="workflow-steps">
        <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Freelance and consulting invoices</h3>
            <p>Track project work, billable hours, fixed-fee services, taxes, and payment notes in a familiar spreadsheet format.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Small business billing</h3>
            <p>Create a repeatable invoice layout for service work, recurring retainers, supplies, and simple client handoffs.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Internal finance prep</h3>
            <p>Use a structured invoice model before moving data into accounting software or client-facing systems.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell section-shell--accent">
    <div class="section-heading section-heading--split">
        <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">What is included</p>
            <h2>A template structure designed for clarity.</h2>
            <p>The initial landing page describes the intended template fields and worksheet organization.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="text-link" href="/ai-excel-formula-generator">Preview Formula Copilot</a>
    </div>
    <div class="template-grid">
        <article>
            <span>Header</span>
            <h3>Business and client details</h3>
            <p>Space for company name, client contact, invoice number, issue date, due date, and payment terms.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>Items</span>
            <h3>Line-item billing table</h3>
            <p>Structured rows for descriptions, quantity, rate, tax treatment, subtotal, and total calculations.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>Summary</span>
            <h3>Tax, discounts, and amount due</h3>
            <p>Clear summary area for subtotal, tax, adjustments, paid amount, balance due, and payment instructions.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>Notes</span>
            <h3>Client-ready context</h3>
            <p>Fields for thank-you notes, purchase order references, delivery details, and late payment reminders.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>Review</span>
            <h3>Pre-send checklist</h3>
            <p>Suggested checks for invoice number, dates, totals, tax assumptions, and client billing details.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>Workflow</span>
            <h3>Excel-first handoff</h3>
            <p>Designed for teams that want a spreadsheet source of truth before PDF export or accounting entry.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Customize</p>
        <h2>How to adapt the invoice template for your workflow.</h2>
        <p>
            The template is planned to be simple enough for everyday users while leaving room for brand, payment,
            and reporting conventions.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-grid">
        <article>
            <span>Brand</span>
            <h3>Add your business identity</h3>
            <p>Update the company name, contact block, invoice accent color, and footer notes to match your client handoff.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>Terms</span>
            <h3>Set payment expectations</h3>
            <p>Adjust payment terms, tax labels, accepted payment methods, late fee language, and purchase order fields.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>Formulas</span>
            <h3>Review totals before sending</h3>
            <p>Use simple formulas for line totals, tax, discounts, balance due, and paid amount tracking.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell section-shell--accent">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
        <h2>Excel invoice template questions.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
        <article>
            <h3>Can I download the invoice template today?</h3>
            <p>No. This PR adds the public landing page only. No file downloads, generation, uploads, or backend processing are connected.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Is this page public and crawlable?</h3>
            <p>Yes. The page is anonymous, indexable, and linked from the Templates page and sitemap.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Who is this invoice template for?</h3>
            <p>It is positioned for freelancers, consultants, service businesses, agencies, and small teams that invoice from spreadsheet workflows.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Does it connect to Stripe or accounting software?</h3>
            <p>No. There is no Stripe, payment, auth, API, or accounting integration in this landing page.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Will it support taxes and discounts?</h3>
            <p>The template positioning includes subtotal, taxes, discounts, paid amount, and amount due fields for future downloadable versions.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Can I use it with Google Sheets?</h3>
            <p>The page is Excel-focused, but the structure is simple enough to inform a future Google Sheets-friendly version.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Template preview</p>
    <h2>Explore more spreadsheet templates and launch plans.</h2>
    <p>
        This invoice template page is a static SEO landing page today. Downloads, payments, accounts, and file
        generation can be added later in separate scoped work.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button button--primary" href="/templates">Back to Templates</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="/pricing">View Pricing Preview</a>
    </div>
</section>
